#. Tag: title
#: ch09.xml:517
#, no-c-format
msgid "The GNU Affero GPL: A Version of the GNU GPL for Server-Side Code"
msgstr ""
"A GNU Affero GPL; unha Versi√≥n da GNU GPL para C√≥digo Executado en Servidor"

#. Tag: para
#: ch09.xml:519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 2007, the Free Software Foundation released a variant of the GPL called "
"the <firstterm>GNU Affero GPL</firstterm> (<ulink url=\"http://www.fsf.org/"
"licensing/licenses/agpl.html\"></ulink>)<footnote><para> The history of the "
"license and its name is a bit complicated. The first version of the license "
"was originally released by Affero, Inc, who based it on the GNU GPL version "
"2. This was commonly referred to as the AGPL. Later, the Free Software "
"Foundation decided to adopt the idea, but by then they had released version "
"3 of their GNU GPL, so they based their new Affero-ized license on that and "
"called it the \"GNU AGPL\". The old Affero license is more or less "
"deprecated now. If you want Affero-like provisions, you should use the GNU "
"version. To avoid ambiguity, call it the \"AGPLv3\", the \"GNU AGPL\", or "
"for maximum precision, \"GNU AGPLv3\".</para></footnote>. Its purpose is to "
"enforce GPL-like sharing provisions on the growing number of companies that "
"offered hosted services&mdash;software that runs on their servers, that "
"users interact with only over the network, and that therefore is never "
"directly distributed to users as executable or source code. Many such "
"services had been using GPL'd software, often with modifications, yet didn't "
"have to share their changes with the world because they weren't distributing "
"any code."
msgstr ""
"En 2007, a Free Software Foundation publicou unha variante da GPL chamada "
"<firstterm>GNU Affero GPL</firstterm> (<ulink url=\"http://www.fsf.org/"
"licensing/licenses/agpl.html\"></ulink>)<footnote><para> A historia desta "
"licenza e do seu nome √© un pouco complicada. A primeira versi√≥n da licenza "
"foi orixinalmente publicada pola empresa Affero Inc. base√°ndose na versi√≥n "
"2 da GNU GPL. Co√±ec√≠ase habitualmente como a AGPL. M√°is tarde, a Free "
"Software Foundation decidiu adoptar a idea, pero por aquel ent√≥n ti√±an "
"liberada a version 3 da s√∫a licenza GNU GPL, polo que basaron a s√∫a "
"licenza \"Afferizada\" na GPL v3 e cham√°ronlle \"GNU AGPL\". A vella "
"licenza Affero est√° m√°is ou menos obsoleta a d√≠a de hoxe. Se queres "
"aseguramentos e seguridades ao estilo dos que che ofrece Affero, deber√≠as "
"empregar a versi√≥n GNU. Para eliminar a ambig√ºidade, ch√°malle \"AGPLv3\", "
"\"GNU AGPL\", ou con m√°xima precisi√≥n \"GNU AGPLv3\".</para></footnote>. O "
"seu obxectivo √© fortalecer a seguridade e garant√≠a de que se comparte o "
"c√≥digo nesta contorna actual dun crecente n√∫mero de empresas que ofrecen "
"os seus servizos dende servidor&mdash; √© dicir, software que corre nos seus "
"servidores, co que os usuarios interactuan unicamente sobre a rede, e que "
"nunca se distrib√∫e directamente aos usuarios nin como c√≥digo executable "
"nin  c√≥digo fonte. Un n√∫mero enorme de servizos estiveron empregando "
"software GPL, habitualmente con modificaci√≥ns, sen ter que compartir os "
"seus cambios co mundo debido a que non estaban distribu√≠ndo ning√∫n c√≥digo "
"(xa que o c√≥digo en cuesti√≥n se executa nos seus servidores e non nos "
"equipos dos usuarios)."

#. Tag: para
#: ch09.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The GNU AGPLv3's solution to this was to take the regular GPL and add a "
"\"Remote Network Interaction\" clause, stating \"<emphasis>...if you modify "
"the Program, your modified version must prominently offer all users "
"interacting with it remotely through a computer network ... an opportunity "
"to receive the Corresponding Source of your version ... at no charge, "
"through some standard or customary means of facilitating copying of software."
"</emphasis>\" This expanded the GPL's enforcement powers into the new world "
"of application service providers. The Free Software Foundation recommends "
"that the GNU AGPLv3 be used for any software that will commonly be run over "
"a network."
msgstr ""
"A soluci√≥n aportada a isto pola GNU AGPLv3 foi coller a GPL e engadirlle "
"unha cl√°usula de \"Interacci√≥n Remota por Rede\" plantexando "
"\"<emphasis>...se ti modificas o Programa, a t√∫a versi√≥n modificada debe "
"ofrecerlle claramente a todos os usuarios que interact√∫en con el "
"remotamente a trav√©s dunha rede de computadores... a oportunidade de "
"recibir o C√≥digo Fonte Correspondente √° t√∫a versi√≥n... sen cargo, a "
"trav√©s dalg√∫n medio est√°ndar ou personalizado para facilitar a copia de "
"software </emphasis>\". Esta cl√°usula expande os poderes de potenciaci√≥n "
"da GPL no novo mundo dos fornecedores de servizos e aplicaci√≥ns pola rede."

#. Tag: para
#: ch09.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the AGPLv3 is not directly compatible with GPLv2 (though it is "
