"some people, the existence of this restriction means the GPL is \"less free"
"\" than more permissive licenses such as the MIT/X license. Where this "
"argument usually goes, of course, is that since \"more free\" must be better "
"than \"less free\" (after all, who's not in favor of freedom?), it follows "
"that those licenses are better than the GPL."
